cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.AR, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the impact of 5G coexistence on existing fixed stations and their deployment strategy. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the interference generated from users towards fixed stations and the attenuation losses at 70/80GHz. 
- cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) is another possible category as the paper focuses on the coexistence of 5G mmWave users with incumbent fixed stations. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve the design and implementation of hardware for 5G mmWave systems. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve the coordination and interaction between multiple agents (i.e., 5G users and fixed stations) in the spectrum access.
